SIMPLE: stereopticon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stereopticon
<hw>Ste`re*op"ti*con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Stereo-</er>, and <er>Optic</er>.]</ety> <def>An instrument,
consisting essentially of a magic lantern in which photographic pictures
are used, by which the image of a landscape, or any object, may be
thrown upon a screen in such a manner as to seem to stand out in relief,
so as to form a striking and accurate representation of the object
itself; also, a pair of magic lanterns for producing the effect of
dissolving views.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stereoscope</ent>⟦br⟧
